Formatting removes the partition tables that allows access to the OS and data.
With special utilites, under correct conditions, training, the partition tables can be restored.
The information on the Recovery Partition contains the orginal install of the system, Operating System, drivers and applications.
Format the drive only if you have created or purchased the Recovery Disks.
Use HP's recovery method --&gt; On boot pressing ''F12 or F10'' (watch for prompt in upper right corner of splash screen) will take you to HPs Recovery Utility.
You will be prompted to perform a Windows Repair or by clicking Advanced a Destructive Restore.
